I see the HX-Trigger format uses `{"announce":"message"}` but the base.html listener expects `e.detail.value`. Let me check the existing announce listener in base.html again.

The listener at `base.html:26-31`:
```js
document.body.addEventListener("announce", function(e) {
    var region = document.getElementById("live-region");
    if (region && e.detail && e.detail.value) {
        region.textContent = e.detail.value;
    }
});
```

And the HX-Trigger header format is `{"announce":"Captured to inbox"}`. When HTMX fires a custom event from an HX-Trigger header with a string value, it puts the value as `e.detail.value`. Wait -- actually, with HTMX, when the trigger value is a plain string like `{"announce":"Captured to inbox"}`, the `e.detail.value` would be `"Captured to inbox"`. That matches the existing todo pattern, so it should work.

Now let me check one more thing -- the delete button's accessible label.
